  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "e2e_node tests on cos-beta-59-9460-20-0 image use GPUs. To install the NVIDIA drivers, we have to disable loadpin which requires a restart. This results in the runner losing connection with the instance which results in the tests failing/erroring.\r\n\r\nOne way to fix this is to make sure that cloud-init has finished before starting the tests.\r\n\r\nSomething like:\r\n```\r\ndiff --git a/test/e2e_node/runner/remote/run_remote.go b/test/e2e_node/runner/remote/run_remote.go\r\nindex 8a1d38daa9..78a5865c9e 100644\r\n--- a/test/e2e_node/runner/remote/run_remote.go\r\n+++ b/test/e2e_node/runner/remote/run_remote.go\r\n@@ -588,6 +588,13 @@ func createInstance(imageConfig *internalGCEImage) (string, error) {\r\n                        err = fmt.Errorf(\"instance %s not running docker daemon - Server not found: %s\", name, output)\r\n                        continue\r\n                }\r\n+               var finished string\r\n+               finished, err = remote.SSH(name, \"ls\", \"/var/lib/cloud/instance/boot-finished\")\r\n+               if err != nil {\r\n+                       err = fmt.Errorf(\"instance %s has not finished cloud-init script: %s\", name, finished)\r\n+                       continue\r\n+               }\r\n                instanceRunning = true\r\n        }\r\n        return name, err\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe need to make sure that we only do this for images which use cloud-init.",
